						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Bhogalinga temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">14th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers to an installation which is not clear in the village Muguḷu-nage which is stated to be amara-grāma by probably Hālabāviyaja.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of about the 14th century A.D.</p>						

